join spaghetti left
spaghetti: Mostly… uh, would calling it ‘spaghetti’ be too meta?
character: …Yeah, probably. So, what? It’s just crochet-gibberish?
spaghetti: Kinda. I know it’s not real knitting, but…
- Sympathize
	character: It’s basically the same to me. Regardless of what you do, it’s probably much better than whatever I could do.
	spaghetti: O-oh! I’m… thank you, I suppose. It’s really not all that hard, though.
	character: It requires dextrous fingers, no? Not many people have those. I’m good with a knife, that’s about as much dexterity as I have.
	I’m sure you’d pick it up easily. See? Look, it’s this simple.
- Deep, Deep thoughts
	character: Isn’t it real knitting? I’m not knowledgeable enough on the arts and crafts of the world, but isn’t thread just a whole bunch of long, fibre noodles? It’s basically spaghetti already, and if you’re making something out of spaghetti, then it’s still spaghetti, just arranged in a different way. Technically, that goes for all things. What if we’re all just made of small, cosmic spaghetti?
	spaghetti: What?
	character: What? Nothing, nothing. That was a joke. I was kidding.
	spaghetti: O- oh…Well! You want to see me make something!? Look!
